 The Drunk and the "Ballerina"
 A fat woman, wearing a sleeveless sun dress, walked into a bar in Dublin.
=20
 She raised her right arm, revealing a hairy armpit, and pointing to all the
people sitting at the bar, asked, 'What man here will buy a lady a drink?'
=20
 The bar went silent as the patrons tried to ignore her.
=20
 But down at the end of the bar, a bleary-eyed drunk slammed his hand down =
on
the counter and bellowed 'Give the ballerina a drink!'=20
=20
 The bartender poured the drink and the woman chugged it down.=20
=20
 She turned to the patrons and again revealing the same hairy armpit, asked,
'What man here will buy a lady a drink?'=20
=20
 Once again, the same drunk slapped his money down on the bar and said, 'Gi=
ve
the ballerina another drink!'=20
=20
 The bartender approached the drunk and said 'Tell me, Paddy, it's your
business if you want to buy the lady a drink, but why do you keep calling
her a
ballerina?'
=20
 The drunk replied, 'Any woman who can lift her leg that high has got to be=
 a
ballerina!'
 Contact: Mick HARKIN
 E-mail: harkin(a)iol.ie
