            <b>'Green Protectionism Folly' Highlighted in Washington
Times Editorial=20
            (??? =96 GW)<br>
            </b>Sustainable Development=92s Tim Wilson authored a recent
editorial=20
            in the Washington Times highlighting the collusion of the
US-based=20
            Blue Green Alliance, Greenpeace and Western retailers like
Staples=20
            and OfficeMax to block exports of Asian pulp and paper
imports. Such=20
            green trade barriers raise costs for consumers in Australia
and the=20
            US, and harm economic growth and job creation in the
developing world.=20
            This coverage follows the recent release of the report, Green
Excuses:=20
            Collusion to Promote Protectionism?<br>
            See: <a
href=3D"http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2010/aug/17/green-protectionist=
-folly/">http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2010/aug/17/<br>
            green-protectionist-folly/</a><br>
            See: <a
href=3D"http://sustainabledev.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/100805-REPORT-=
