            <b>Integrated Pest Management in Europe: The ENDURE Network
of Excellence=20
            shares the fruits of four years=92 research with the crop
protection=20
            community<br>
            </b>24-25 November 2010 - PARIS<br>
            European Union Member States are currently working on the
implementation=20
            of the Framework Directive on the sustainable use of
pesticides to=20
            make Integrated Pest Management become a field reality by
2014. Major=20
            efforts in research and development are called for to
accompany this=20
            initiative and help mainstream IPM.<br>
            ENDURE (Project number: 031499 =96 ENDURE -6th Framework
Programme =96=20
            Thematic Priority 5 &quot;FOOD and Quality and Safety&quot;)
believes=20
            we can take advantage of the diversity of experiences, tools
and strategies=20
            across Europe and build synergies to make crop protection
more compatible=20
            with our new environmental goals while maintaining our
competitiveness.<br>
            That=92s what ENDURE has been working on since 2007 and the
international=20
            conference, which is being organised by INRA, will provide
the opportunity=20
            for the Network of Excellence to share the fruits of four
years=92 research=20
            with the crop protection community.<br>
            The event will provide farmers, advisers, policy makers,
researchers=20
            and representatives of the farm supply chain and food retail
sectors=20
            across Europe with the opportunity to better appreciate,
critique,=20
            feed into and benefit from our research strategies and
outputs. It=20
            will also provide a preview of, and help us improve, the
future permanent=20
            European Research Group that will maintain, update and enrich
the=20
            resources made available by ENDURE.<br>
            No registration fees are being charged for this event, though
registration=20
            remains compulsory. Book your place now at: <a
href=3D"https://colloque.inra.fr/endure2010">https://colloque.inra.fr/endur=
e2010</a>.<br>
            See:
<a href=3D"http://www.endure-network.eu/">http://www.endure-network.eu</a><=
br>
            Contacts: Philippe DELVAL, Andrew LEWER<br>
            E-mail: philippe.delval(a)acta.asso.fr,
andrew.lewer(a)cirad.fr<br>
