            <font size=3D"3" face=3D"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>
            <b>The Drunk and the &quot;Ballerina&quot;<br>
            </b>A fat woman, wearing a sleeveless sun dress, walked into a =
bar=20
            in Dublin.<br>
            <br>
            She raised her right arm, revealing a hairy armpit, and pointin=
g to=20
            all the people sitting at the bar, asked, 'What man here will b=
uy=20
            a lady a drink?'<br>
            <br>
            The bar went silent as the patrons tried to ignore her.<br>
            <br>
            But down at the end of the bar, a bleary-eyed drunk slammed his=
 hand=20
            down on the counter and bellowed 'Give the ballerina a drink!' =
<br>
            <br>
            The bartender poured the drink and the woman chugged it down. <=
br>
            <br>
            She turned to the patrons and again revealing the same hairy ar=
mpit,=20
            asked, 'What man here will buy a lady a drink?' <br>
            <br>
            Once again, the same drunk slapped his money down on the bar an=
d said,=20
            'Give the ballerina another drink!' <br>
            <br>
            The bartender approached the drunk and said 'Tell me, Paddy, it=
's=20
            your business if you want to buy the lady a drink, but why do y=
ou=20
            keep calling her a ballerina?'<br>
            <br>
            The drunk replied, 'Any woman who can lift her leg that high ha=
s got=20
            to be a ballerina!'<br>
